"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H19205783\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What are inhalers?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Inhalers are devices with medicine in them. They are used to treat lung conditions that can make it hard to breathe, such as:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Asthma",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD)",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Doctors also sometimes prescribe inhalers to treat a cough caused by a lung infection called bronchitis.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H19205790\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Are there different types of inhalers?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. There are 2 main types of inhalers. The 2 main types are:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Metered dose inhalers (",
"        <a class=\"graphic graphic_picture graphicRef61575 \" href=\"UTD.htm?36/35/37439\">",
"         picture 1",
"        </a>",
"        )",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Dry powder inhalers (",
"        <a class=\"graphic graphic_picture graphicRef67084 \" href=\"UTD.htm?0/19/306\">",
"         picture 2",
"        </a>",
"        )",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      People might need to use more than 1 inhaler to treat their condition.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H19205797\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How do inhalers work?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Inhalers work by spraying medicine that a person then breathes into his or her lungs. But metered dose inhalers and dry powder inhalers spray medicine in different ways.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Most metered dose inhalers spray medicine when a person presses down on the top of the canister.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Dry powder inhalers spray medicine when a person takes a deep breath in from the inhaler. (One metered dose inhaler works the same way as dry powder inhalers.)",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H19205804\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How do I use an inhaler?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;The directions for using metered dose inhalers and dry powder inhalers are different. Your doctor or nurse will show you how to use your inhaler.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      It&rsquo;s important to follow all your doctor&rsquo;s directions when you use your inhaler, so that the medicine gets into your lungs.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H19205811\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       When should I use my inhaler?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Your doctor or nurse will make a treatment plan that tells you when to use your inhaler. Some inhalers are used right away when symptoms start, to treat those symptoms. Other inhalers are used every day, to help control symptoms long-term and prevent future symptoms.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      If you have any questions about when or how to use your inhaler, talk with your doctor or nurse.",
"     </p>",
